                <head type="title"><persName corresp="#ETC">E. T. Cook</persName> (1857&#x2013;1919)</head>
                <p>Over the ten&#x2010;year period of work on the <title type="book" corresp="JRWORKSLE">Library Edition</title>, <persName corresp="#ETC">Cook</persName> worked
                    eight hours per day, while maintaining his position as a lead writer for the <title type="periodical" corresp="#LONDONDAILYCHRONICLE"><hi
                        rend="italic">Daily Chronicle</hi></title>. He also authored his <title type="book" corresp="#COOKLIFEOFRUSKIN"><hi rend="italic"
                        >Life of Ruskin</hi></title> and other works on <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>.</p>
                <p><persName corresp="#JSD">Dearden</persName>, <title type="book" corresp="#DEARDENRUSKINLIBRARY">&#x201C;Library Edition of the Works of John Ruskin&#x201D;</title>,
                    56.</p>
